President George W. Bush visited Camp Victory near Baghdad airport, greeted troops, and signed a pact giving Iraq veto power over US troop operations.
During a press conference with Prime Minister Maliki, an Iraqi journalist threw shoes at Bush, calling him a "dog."
Bush dodged the shoes, highlighting the ongoing hostility towards him.
Despite the incident, Bush defended the war, citing its necessity for US security and Iraqi stability.
The shoe-throwing incident symbolized the conflicted views towards Bush in Iraq.
The trip, overshadowed by the incident, emphasized the complexities and challenges faced during Bush's presidency.
